Head of Greek Church to Travel to Germany for Medical Tests

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 
2011-09-21T06:41:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/head-of-greek-church-to-travel-to-germany-for-medical-tests.html
The Archbishop of  Athens  and All
 Greece  Hieronymos II is travelling to  Germany  for medical tests,
the  Archdiocese of Athens  said in a statement on its web site.  The Archbishop has been suffering from persistent fever and
an infection, the state-run Athens News Agency reported today.
Hieronymos has been head of the Orthodox Church in Greece since
February 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
